FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - KYRGYZSTAN
=================================
Date: Fri, 11 Apr 1997 10:55:39 -0400
To: mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Subject: Today's OIE report

11 April 1997
Vol. 10 - No. 15
FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE IN KYRGYZSTAN
Emergency report
Translation of a communication received on 9 April 1997 from Dr B.M.
Murataliev, Director General of Veterinary Services, Bishkek:
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 7 February 1997.
Estimated date of first infection: 25 January 1997.
Location city of Osh
No.of outbreaks 1
Description of affected population: privately owned mixed-bred cattle of
various ages, kept confined by their respective owners. The disease was
reported in a backyard in the city of Osh.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species bovine
susceptible 514
cases 3
deaths ...
destroyed ...
slaughtered ...
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Osh Regional Veterinary Laboratory.
B. Diagnostic tests used: tests for specific antigens and antibodies.
C. Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus type O.
Source of agent / origin of infection: sick animals purchased in a
neighbouring country were introduced in Kyrgyzstan without the authorisation
of the Veterinary Services.
Control measures during reporting period: application of quarantine in the
city of Osh; vaccination of all susceptible animals in the city of Osh and
the adjacent districts.
---
